<p>President Javier Milei&#x27;s La Libertad Avanza scored a decisive midterm victory, strengthening his ability to protect vetoes and press ahead with wide-ranging economic reforms after voters backed his agenda in nationwide elections . International markets responded positively on Monday, with Argentine bonds, equities and the peso rallying after the results were announced . The outcome also highlighted public backing for Milei&#x27;s shock-therapy approach and underscored the political impact of open U.S. support from President Trump, which analysts and commentators said helped shape the result .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/8AyCMUzgUAafaVDjd96leX-2bzQs7PnVxWv3H5az9SdbDxX0pzlq-0FIyandHsfEa6IGjjTEUcGBWuSnYPn5iH3uRph4iS78DnwQVRIpvR2IqJjF0iykD3KNoaafg6fDK2p0ApYuhBWUMzpWPAVz270QI_uuCLOm_sWdOr-pyms7GiLbdJbRCvK4B96qDzvX6qB7NvFzO-4' alt='President Javier Milei celebrating election results with supporters in Buenos Aires on Sunday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Market reaction: Argentina&#x27;s bonds, stocks and currency jumped on Monday as investors priced in greater policy certainty after the midterms</li><li>Seat gains: La Libertad Avanza roughly tripled its lower-house representation — rising from 37 to about 101 seats in party tallies reported by some outlets — and expanded in the Senate as well, improving its parliamentary leverage</li><li>Turnout anomaly: Voter turnout was reported just under 68% despite Argentina&#x27;s compulsory voting rules, a historically low participation level for a nationwide vote</li><li>Policy track record: Since taking office in 2023, Milei has pursued deep spending cuts and public-sector layoffs while taking steps that supporters credit with reducing runaway inflation</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Supporters of Javier Milei: Many voters continued to back the president&#x27;s economic overhaul and libertarian experiment, seeing it as a break from past policies . (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/26/world/americas/argentina-election-javier-milei.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li><li>President Donald Trump / U.S. administration: U.S. backing and public signals from President Trump were credited by some analysts with strengthening Milei&#x27;s position during the campaign . (<a href='https://www.ft.com/content/395d26c9-2f4f-4b86-9e80-65ed2d5ab0bc'>Financial Times; France 24</a>)</li><li>Critics and international commentators: Some commentators argued that U.S. financial support effectively tilted the playing field and warned about the social cost of harsh austerity measures . (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627021-us-exported-democracy-argentina/'>RT</a>)</li><li>Financial markets / investors: Traders reacted by bidding up Argentine assets, interpreting the legislative gains as lowering policy risk for Milei&#x27;s reform agenda . (<a href='https://www.allsides.com/news/2025-10-27-0700/foreign-policy-argentine-markets-soar-after-president-javier-mileis-midterm-victory-milei-thanks-president-trump'>AllSides; Financial Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.csmonitor.com/Commentary/the-monitors-view/2025/1027/Patience-pays-off-in-Argentina'>Patience pays off in Argentina</a> - csmonitor.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/395d26c9-2f4f-4b86-9e80-65ed2d5ab0bc'>Markets surge on Argentine election results</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/26/world/americas/argentina-election-javier-milei.html'>Javier Milei’s Party Triumphs in Argentina Midterm Election</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627021-us-exported-democracy-argentina/'>The US has exported democracy again. Not with bombs this time, but that doesn’t make it better</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.allsides.com/news/2025-10-27-0700/foreign-policy-argentine-markets-soar-after-president-javier-mileis-midterm-victory-milei-thanks-president-trump'>Argentine Markets Soar After President Javier Milei&#x27;s Midterm Victory; Milei Thanks President Trump</a> - allsides.com</li><li><a href='https://www.economist.com/the-americas/2025/10/27/el-boletin-newsletter-the-fallout-from-javier-mileis-big-win'>El Boletín newsletter: The fallout from Javier Milei’s big win</a> - economist.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/tv-shows/the-debate/20251028-trump-backing-boosts-milei-in-midterm-elections-an-offer-argentina-couldn-t-refuse'>Trump backing boosts Milei in midterm elections: An offer Argentina couldn&#x27;t refuse?</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/trump-says-milei-had-%27a-lot-of-help%27-from-us-for-argentina-election-win1'>Trump says Milei had &#x27;a lot of help&#x27; from U.S. for Argentina election win</a> - japantoday.com</li></ul>